<FONT SIZE=+1>COVER STORY</FONT>
<p>
<blockquote>
<B><I>See How They Run</I></B><br>
In addition to <b>Rich Lowry's</B> Website 
<a href="/nationalreview/29july96/feature.html">Feature Article</a> on the search for Bob Dole's running mate, <B>Ramesh Ponnuru</B> looks at the female possibilities and finds them unattractive...<B>Kate O'Beirne</B> picks the top ten conservative contenders.
</blockquote>
<P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>ARTICLES</FONT>
<P>
<blockquote>
<B><I>On the Scene</I></B><br>
<B>Rosemary Jencks</B> wonders if Richard Lamm will be Perot's puppet or his replacement...<B>David Satter</B> scours through the rubble of the Russian elections...<B>Andrew Stuttaford</B> believes in skeptics.
<P>
<B><I>What's the Big Idea?</I></B><br>
After the collapse of socialism, Europeans continue to flirt with disaster and the Left, reports <B>Anthony de Jasay</B>.
<P>
<B><I>Netanyahu Rampant</I></B><br>
Are Israeli hawks in the ascendant? <B>Amos Perlmutter</B> examines how Benjamin Netanyahu hopes to combine security peace.
<P>
<B><I>Smoking Wars</I></B><br>
Media reporting on smoking is hazardous to the truth, says <B>Jacob Sullum</B>.  
<P>
<B><I>Illiberal Court</I></B><br>
<B>David Forte</B> fingers the Supreme Court as a domestic enemy of the constitutional Republic.
</blockquote>
<P>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>BOOKS, ARTS & MANNERS</FONT>
<P><blockquote>
How has Clinton made us despise him? <B>Ramesh Ponnuru</B> counts the ways, with help from Jeffrey H. Birnbaum's <I>Madhouse</I>, Richard Reeves's <I>Running in Place</I>, Paul Greenberg's <I>No Surprises</I>, Bob Woodward's <I>The Choice</I>, Haynes Johnson and David Broder's <I>The System</I>, and Tim Graham's <I>Pattern of Deception</I>....<B>Digby Anderson</B> flicks <I>Ashes to Ashes</I>, Richard Kluger's superflous history of the smoking wars....Must religious claims be provable? <B>J. Budziszewski</B> takes a practical look at the religious pragmatism of Luke Timothy Johnson's <I>The Real Jesus</I> and Carol Zaleski's <I>The Life of the World to Come</I>....Almost everything you <I>think</I> you know about the Olympics isn't so. <B>Richard Grenier</B> explains....<B>John Simon</B> wishes on a <I>Lone Star</I>. <I>Phenomenon</I> is an overstatement.
<P>
<B><I>The Misanthrope's Corner</I></B><br>
<B>Florence King</B> wonders why politicians are so common.</blockquote>
<P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>SECTIONS</FONT>
<P><blockquote><B><I>
Letters<br>
From the Editor<br>
For the Record<br>
<a href="/nationalreview/29july96/week.html">
The Week</a><br>
Gekko<br>
help<br>
