<head><title>Rusty -- NR</title></head>
<body>
<center>
<h2>Rusty</h2>
<hr></center>
<P>



Well, Tipper was right again! She told me this morning that if I cleaned out the basement, I'd be surprised by what turned up. So down I went with a box and a mess of recyclable trash bags and a reluctant Al Jr. And boy! do we Gores have a messy basement!
<P>But since it's snowing like the dickens out and since Al Jr.'s soccer game (St. Alban's vs. Calvert) was called off due to snowdrifts five feet high (the tallest kid on Al's team is 4'11"), the Gore men weren't that unhappy to do some early spring cleaning.
<P>We found the usual basement stuff: solar hats, earth brick molds, planetary communication panels, that kind of thing. But behind a box of copies of Earth in the Balance, we found a box of notes that look like they could belong to you -- they're handwritten, and written in some form of scientific notation, I think; at least, I can't make heads or tails out of it:
<P>2/23/93
<br>HRC -- v. upst. Scrmng. Rd fcd. Snrlng. Thrwng lmp @ potus.
<br>Wnts WHTrvl Offc ``hng out 2 dry.''
<br>Hrry Thmsn nds $$$$$$ for trvl/chrtr/whtevr.
<br>$$$$$$$ more $$$$$$$ more $$$$$$$.
<p>Does any of that make sense to you? It looks to me like some kind of complicated photosynthesis thing.
<p>We also found a stack of computer printouts. Here's one of them.
<br>RSE LW FRM -- BILLING/PROJECT CODE/HRS
<br>HRC -- WhtWtr/CstlGrnd/McDgl/et al -- 110 hrs @ $350 
<br>HRC -- rprsntg WhtWtr to Gov -- 110 hrs @ $350
<p>These go on and on. Stacks and stacks of them. Could they be the baby-sitting ledger for one of the girls?
<p>And then we found some more handwritten notes.
<p>9/12/93
<br>Frst Ldy v. upst. Scrmg. Shtng. Thrwng plts & bwls & portrt of Lincln & scrmng & cllng me a ``gd 4 nthg'' and tllng me 2 ``fall on the grnade.'' & sayng that the $$$ for cttle futrs not the only $$$, so ``smll the cffee u dmbsht.'' Potus jst sttng thr, prtndng nt to hr.
<br>Frst ldy syng v.fos ``did the rt thng'' and ``prvd hs lylty.''
<br>Frst ldy syng mr $$$$ and $$$$ and need $$$$ ``vacum'' offc and dsk of v.fos, ``sck'' the files in Rse Lw Frm. ``Shrd evrythng!!!''
<br>Frst ldy clls potus ``wshy wshy gd 4 nthg ld around by his 'trsr snk.' Portrt of Thos. Jeffrsn slmmd in2 wall.
<br>Mttng ends. No actn tkn.
<p>Does any of that make sense to you, Rusty? Could it be something the Quayles forgot to take?
<p>The strange thing is, I was just down here a few weeks ago and I didn't notice all of this junk cluttering the place up. And when Tipper ordered me to clean up the basement, it was like she knew that all of these boxes and papers were here, even though as far as I know, she hasn't been down here for ages. 
<p>``What's down there, Tip?'' I asked.
<p>``Our last hope,'' she said. You know women, Rusty. It's like they have some kind of sixth sense for housecleaning. 
<p>The next thing that turned up was a computer disk, which Al Jr. happily ``hacked'' his way into. The screen on his laptop just sprang alive -- numbers and figures zooming by. All I caught was: 
<p>TO: B.C. & H.R.C.
<p>FR: H.Th. & L. B-Th. 
<p>Attached please find profit projections for Air Thomason, Inc. Please initial and route to M. McL. and D. Watkins. 
<p>Then some sort of spreadsheet program began, and the numbers kept getting larger and larger.
<p>And the last scrap of paper -- and this one really might be important -- 
<p>IOU $30,000 for re-election Gov. Ark.
<p>Redeemable in cash or in kind.
<p>I'm tempted to recycle most of this -- we should be encouraging people to e-mail whenever they can, and so if whoever it belongs to comes back looking for it, well, let them learn the hard way.
<p>There was also a giant box of computer diskettes, but I gave them all to Al Jr., who's merrily erasing them so he can use them to save his ``Zoop'' games.
<p>I still haven't decided what to do with all of this paper, though. Maybe I'll ask Tipper to handle it. After all, she's the one who sent me down here in the first place. She'll know what to do with
it.
</body>
